AGI - "After 898 days from the presentation of the preliminary project and 349 days from the request for verification submitted by us, on 19 March the Municipality of Rome communicates the start of a verification for the presence of a 'presunta area boscata' of 2 hectares, > also raised from AS Roma but always denied by the Municipality. Denunce, distrust and exposed have finally knocked down the rubber wall raised by the administration of Rome Capital to protect the narrative that wanted to show the area of Pietralata as a degraded area and to retrain". This is how the post published this morning by the coordination of the citizens "Yes' to the Park, Yes' to the Hospital, No to the Stadium" > which is monitoring the process and the realization of the new plant of the yellow club in the area of the former Sdo of Pietralata>, which should be completed in 2027. The post published on Facebook also shows the communication between the offices. Last night Campidoglio and AS Roma had assured that there is no "some kind of delay" in the planned activities, and that "the planning of the interventions for archaeological investigations is ongoing". > &nbsp;
&nbsp; "After having communicated 'the resumption of the excavations from 17 February' then become '24 March' - recalls the Coordination -, after having submitted a 'request of formal consent to the activities of demolition or cutting of trees', rejected to the sender with a ban on the cutting of protected trees and the conglomerates arbustivi, on 19 March As Roma has received a formal stop for the execution of the We are sure that the concurrent with the opening of an investigation by the Prosecution > has led to more mild advice those managers who, until yesterday, have always responded to the most disparate motives such as, for example, the absence of a forest whose verification, however, had never been implemented by anyone".
<br> "We are happy to have led the Commune in a logical choice - the post continues - but that it does not satisfy us at all seen the obsessive allowed for the start of the activities on the free areas despite the beginning of the nesting period, which should involve the interruption of any cutting or tearing activity on all Rome at least until 31 July, > as provided by the Rules of Green of the City of Rome. We shall report in a proxy any activity > or authorization that entails the change of the status of the places to date present in the area in question and we shall be in possession of a second agronomic expertise, carried out as a primary figure of the sector, which we will integrate with the documentation already filed in prosecutor for the file opened following the note of the State Forestry Corps. Voler build a stadium on a green area destined to park> where there is a forest is a shame."

