AGI - A girl was stabbed this afternoon on the Gazzi avenue, in Messina, and died. The young, a twenty-year-old native to the province of Palermo, an intern of the Polyclinic, had been rescued and transported to the nearby Polyclinic but for her there was nothing to do.
The attack occurred on the Gazzi avenue near the side entrance of the "G.Celeste" stage. The girl, according to the account of some witnesses, had a deep neck wound.» He took a few steps and blinded himself. According to a first reconstruction, a boy would try to chase the attacker on foot. Carabinieri.&nbsp operate on the premises;
The murdered girl is Sara Campanella. "I'm speechless," said the mayor of Messina, Federico Basile. "Today - he added - Messina was shaken by an immense tragedy: A young life, Sara Campanella's, was brutally broken. The violence of this gesture leaves us unbelieving and deeply grieved. I want to express my closeness to Sara's family and friends. At this time of unbearable pain, know that the city of Messina is with you. We condemn this act of violence with all force and trust that justice can take its course."
